RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WIN DIXIE RONNIE pressed Sea Pearl from the outside, took command just inside the eighth pole and edged away to be clear under strong encouragement. SEA PEARL vied for the early lead while racing near the rail, dug in nearing the eighth pole but was no match for the winner late while holding the place position. POLITICAL ASTRAY stalked the top pair, moved up to challenge the leader three deep near the quarter pole but couldn't match strides with the top two in the drive but kept on willingly to the wire. VERIFIABLE broke awkwardly, raced near the back of the pack after the poor start, moved up five wide into the upper stretch and raced evenly late. KAZILLION raced off the early going, was near the inside around the far turn through the stretch run and lacked a bid. FOR THE THRILL was coaxed along from the inside and weakened through the drive. ROMANCE IN HABANA raced mid pack, hard ridden into the far turn, raced three to two wide in the stretch run and had no late response. MYSTICAL LADY raced in tight quarters soon after the start while being crowded by Gilded Chammrose, trailed early on, angled in race near the inside around the far turn into the upper stretch and never menaced. GILDED CHARMROSE hustled from the outside, raced five to six wide into the upper stretch and never threatened.

ENTRY.OWNER: David Fawkes Racing Inc and Schwartz Darrin

ENTRY.NAME: Verifiable
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke awkwardly, off pace, 5wd upper stretch, even late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LASSO dropped back early while under pressure, moved up into the far turn, altered out just past the quarter pole, circled the field from the far outside and finished strongly to surge clear under steady handling. EL ROJO VIVO chased the top pair from the inside early, hard ridden into the far turn, raced three deep nearing the quarter pole, was off the inside in the stretch run and kept on gamely to the wire. CINCO HARLEY dueled near the rail early on, headed into the upper stretch, led near the eighth pole and gave way grudgingly late. A G DIAMOND was shuffled back at the start, ridden along early near the inside, experienced traffic near the eighth pole, angled out to race three to four wide between rivals and kept on willingly to the wire. Jockey of A G Diamond claimed objection for interference against El Rojo Vivo and stewards ruled no change. MR. LEFTY hustled early while racing mid pack, raced from the outside in the stretch, shifted near the sixteenth pole and kept on showing good late interest. Jockey of Mr. Lefty claimed objection against El Rojo Vivo for interference in the stretch run and stewards ruled no change. UNEQUIVOCALLY dueled outside of foe and faded in the latter stages. DESTINO raced far back and never threatened.
